-*- How do I set up a listbox so that it shows the name of an item,
but provides an ID number to my access basic function, instead of
providing the items name?

This is a very common occurance. You have a table with two fields,
ItemName and ItemID. You wish the user to be able to select an item by
name, but you wish your program to use the ItemID to find and perform
an action on that item. Set the Number of Columns property to 2, the
Column Width to "0 in; 2 in", and set the Bound Column property to
2. Now set the Recordsourse property to a query, whose first two
printed fields are ItemID and ItemName. 

Now the listbox will only show item names, but when you get the value
of Me!LbxItems you will get the ItemID.
